OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F465A1773843068
OL,3,CTwo Cardiff secondary schools remain
OL,4,Cclosed after weapon threats made
OL,6,FIn its latest update, shared by
OL,7,FCardiff Council ward councillor for
OL,8,FRhiwbina Jayne Cowan, South Wales
OL,9,FPolice said the sender of the threats
OL,10,F"remains unidentified with
OL,11,Fcommunications routed through
OL,12,Fanonymised VPN services."
OL,14,FA multi-agency assessment has
OL,15,Fdetermined that the threats "are
OL,16,Fdisruptive rather than credible",
OL,17,Fsomething that has been reinforced by
OL,18,Fsearches carried out at the school and
OL,19,Fintelligence gathered, the update
OL,20,Fadded.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
